<br>
I just dont buy the idea that with 10,000 people on a server or whatever one guy moving with all gear dropable and non dropable is gonna hurt the econ. <br>
<br>
The only people benefiting under the current system are those who have already done the under the table move. Opening it up to everyone will even the field as to those people.<br>
<br>
The guy who thinks that the exp gains on Sullon overcome the fact that you get trained and have to pvp all the time at a moment notice is completly wrong.<br>
<br>
The best geared player on SZ probably does not even make the top 200 server wide. Sullon may NEVER have a guild in PoTime. Its SZ that gets hurt by moves TO it, no blue server has to fear people going FROM SZ to their server. Although with the new dungeons thing coming in the fall there might be places to level that are pvp free (currently you cannot get any exp in a pvp free zone) which could change that.<br>
