Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ajilon>Ajilon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>KAfekinBOOM!</span><br>  Posts: 852<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 1:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Sam, PoP flags go with even on naked server moves today, so I'm relatively sure that IF Sony ever allowed the +gear moves flags would still go.<br>
<br>
Also I'm not debating whether or not you &quot;earned&quot; your levels despite xp bonus's because of the pvp, I'm just saying that the different rule sets would probably be used as a reason by Sony to exclude Sullon Zek IF +gear moves become policy.<br>
<br>
<br>
As a side note, it's a bad business decision on Sony's part not to allow the +gear moves, I saw an article where John Smedley (fuzzy memory, pretty sure it was Smed, maybe someone still has a link to that article?) said they had made a million dollars so far just on the name change and server moves service.  Think about it... now imagine how many people would be willing to start playing again, or server move and continue playing (and paying subscriptions again) if they were allowed to move servers and keep the gear they worked on.  <br>
<br>
IF/when the +gear moves become policy watch the price go up also, probably in the neighborhood of an additional $25-50.  Easily justified to from their point of view, it's not just a script, they are going to say it requires extra GM/Admin manhours to correct mistakes the script makes (which will in fact happen) So they will double the price of the moves and double their money, while in reality the scripts will probably run fairly smoothly.  The biggest hit they'll take on GM manhours will come from the volume increase of server move requests.<br>
